The paper deals with low probability of detection (LPD) communication, which is a topic closely related to information theory and cryptography. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses the impact of secretly pre-arranging the time of communication, which is a technique used in covert communication and can be considered a form of security through obscurity. This makes cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) another likely category. The paper also mentions AWGN channels, which are commonly used in multimedia communication, suggesting cs.MM (Multimedia) as a possible category. The paper also discusses the use of covert communication to evade detection, which is a topic relevant to network security, making cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) another possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the effectiveness of the warden's detector, which is a topic related to signal processing and detection theory, making cs.SI (Signal Processing) a possible category as well.
